There's a worker fixing the kitchen floor, and I'm pretending to work from home, actually editing 'Can't Stop Won't Stop'.
If only this damned file could open (OneDrive is really crap).
*Hackers' voices* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the noise is super loud. Great.
Turned the air purifier to max, feels a bit too intense, but I do smell wood shavings, so it's not entirely unreasonable, especially since he opposes wearing a mask. And I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but he had to leave for me to sleep.
The good news is that Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter 5 is very long and makes people super anxious. Yes! It's so exciting.
Looking for and replacing……➡️ellipsis, this chapter has 54 of them 😅
But I still want to stick to this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repairman is using a vacuum cleaner to clean, hoping that means he's almost done.
He's out (sounds like he's) cutting something. I sneaked a peek at the progress. Still a lot of work to do :(.
The fifth chapter has 7 pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the document state is quite good, mainly just formatting adjustments and some small changes to the active voice and concision. But I really need a break, have a cup of tea, and that guy is still working in my kitchen.
He's started using the vacuum cleaner again. Let's hope that's a good omen.
The worker fixing the kitchen floor has left!
He told me he's fixing the entire floor, but the landlord is too stingy and only wants to pay for the repair of the rotten part near the entrance. Feels much better.
I'm having tea in the garden, and the air purifier in the kitchen is working hard to purify the air in the room!
